// This is a text file with instructions to create a simple lock-on indicator prefab manually

HOW TO CREATE LOCK-ON INDICATOR MANUALLY:

1. CREATE NEW GAME OBJECT:
   - Right-click in Hierarchy → Create Empty
   - Name it "SimpleLockOnIndicator"

2. ADD SPRITE RENDERER:
   - Select SimpleLockOnIndicator
   - Add Component → Rendering → Sprite Renderer
   - Set Sprite to any simple sprite (circle, crosshair, etc.)
   - Set Color to Red (255, 0, 0, 255)

3. ADD LOCK-ON INDICATOR SCRIPT:
   - Add Component → Scripts → LockOnIndicator
   - The script will auto-configure itself

4. SCALE IT:
   - Set Transform Scale to (0.5, 0.5, 0.5)

5. MAKE IT A PREFAB:
   - Drag from Hierarchy to Project folder
   - Delete from Hierarchy (we just want the prefab)

6. ASSIGN TO LOCK-ON SYSTEM:
   - Find your Nyx child object
   - In NyxLockOnSystem component
   - Set "Lock On Indicator Prefab" to your new prefab
   - Check "Use World Space Indicator"

7. TEST:
   - Press RB/LB on controller OR scroll mouse wheel
   - Should see red circle above enemies 